from sasghm gary merrill subject re jigger i may not be the world greatest expert on chigger a type of mite indigenou to the south but i certainly have spend a lot of time contemplate the little bugger over the past six year since we move to here be some observation gain from painful experience reaction to chigger vary greatly from person to person some person get tiny red bite other like me be more sensitive and get fairly large swell sore-like affair chigger bite be the gift that keep on give i swear that these thing will itch for month there be a lot of folklore about chigger i think most of it be fiction i have try to do research on the critter since they have such an effect on me the only book i could find on the subject wa a single book in unc special collection library i have not yet go through what be require to get it based on my experience and that of my family member the old folk remedy of fingernail polish simply do work i recall read that the theory upon which it be base that the chigger burrow into ymy skin and continue to party there be false i think it be more likely that the reaction be to toxin of some sort the little pest release but thi be speculation the best approach be prevention a couple of thing work well a good insect repellent deet such a deep wood off liberally apply to ankle waistband etc be a good start there be another preparation call chig away that be a combination of sulfur and some kind of cream cortisone that originally wa prepare for the army and be not commercially available in the summer i put thi on my ankle every morning when i get up on weekend since i literally ca go outside where we live in the country without seriou consequence they apparently do like sulfur much at all you can use sulfur a a dust on ymy body or clothe to repel them no amount of prevention will be completely successful forget the fingernail polish i have finally settle upon a treatment that involf topical application of a combination of cortisone creme reduce the inflamation and swell and benzocaine relieve the itch i wo tell you all the thing i try nor will i tell you some of the thing my wife do since thi count a minor surgery and be best not mention i also think it gain nothing the swell and itch can also be significantly relieve by the application of hot pack and thi seem to speed recovery a well doctor seem not to care much about chigger the urban and suburban doctor apparently do encounter them much and the rural doctor seem to regard them a a force of nature that one must endure i suspect that anyone who could come up with a good treatment for chigger would make a lot of money gary h merrill principal system developer c compiler development sa institute inc sa campu dr cary nc sasghm mcnc sa sasghm 